Build a production-quality local web application: a real-time Kubernetes/OpenShift log explorer designed for developers.

The tool should feel like a hybrid between Kibana, VSCode DevTools, and a modern real-time chat interface — but lightweight, local, and built only on "oc logs".

---

🧱 Tech Stack

Frontend

- React (Vite)
- TypeScript
- TailwindCSS
- shadcn/ui (UI components)
- Zustand (state management)
- react-window (virtualized rendering)
- WebSocket client

Backend

- Node.js (LTS)
- Express (minimal API layer)
- ws (WebSocket server)
- child_process.spawn (for "oc logs")
- No external logging infrastructure

---

🧠 Core Architecture

oc logs -f
   ↓
Node streaming layer
   ↓
Log processing + enrichment engine
   ↓
Sliding time window buffer
   ↓
UI state manager (filter/sort/view state)
   ↓
WebSocket
   ↓
React UI

---

⏳ SLIDING TIME WINDOW (DYNAMIC & REQUIRED)

- Logs are stored only for a time-based window
- Default: 30 minutes

Supported values:

- 1 min
- 5 min
- 15 min
- 30 min
- 1 hour
- custom input

Behavior:

- Logs outside window are automatically removed from view
- Changing window updates UI instantly
- No fixed-size buffers allowed

---

🚨 CRITICAL UX RULE

SINGLE POD CONTEXT MODEL (MANDATORY)

- Only ONE pod active at any time
- Switching pod MUST:
  - immediately clear UI
  - reset buffer
  - stop previous stream
  - start new stream

No multi-pod mixing allowed.

